definition: to complete the last stage of work/to round off
horse's tail/pointed posterior section of a locust etc
tail/remainder/remnant/extremity/sixth of the 28 constellations/classifier for fish

sentences.english: The first-phase construction has entered the last step.
sentences.chinese: 一期工程已進入掃尾階段。

sentences.english: This would be the last paragraph in "Overdue";
I’m still cleaning my post-vacation backlog of feeds and messages.
sentences.chinese: 長假後攢了一堆待閱內容和信息，掃尾工作還在繼續。

sentences.english: In 2006, Shakespeare plans to round off the category with four new models.
sentences.chinese: 2006年，莎士比亞計劃掃尾類四個新的模式。

sentences.english: Feel small, is the beginning of great harvestFeel small, is the beginning of great harvest.
sentences.chinese: 感到本人微小的時候，纔是宏大收穫的掃尾。
